law.catch_line: The guilt or innocence of the accused of the crime charged may not be inquired into by the Governor ...
law.text: The guilt or innocence of the accused of the crime charged may not be inquired into by the Governor or in any proceeding after the demand for extradition, accompanied by a charge of crime in legal form as provided in this title, has been presented to the Governor, except as it may be involved in identifying the accused as the person charged with the crime.
